02:25.880 --> 02:27.950
Justine, please.

02:31.400 --> 02:34.233
It's called "stimming,"
self-stimulation.

02:34.920 --> 02:37.912
Whereas you and I might tap our fingers,

02:38.080 --> 02:40.548
grind our teeth, bite our nails,

02:40.760 --> 02:42.478
your son rocks back and forth.

02:42.680 --> 02:45.433
It's more obvious, but perfectly natural.

02:45.640 --> 02:49.076
We came here because
we heard you specialized in...

02:49.240 --> 02:51.117
What is it? What does he have?

02:51.280 --> 02:53.919
I'm not a fan of labels, ma'am.

02:54.600 --> 02:57.273
Your son is a remarkable young man.

02:57.440 --> 03:00.193
Who goes crazy
when you turn the vacuum on.

03:00.360 --> 03:03.432
He wears one T-shirt,
won't let you hug him.

03:03.600 --> 03:05.431
Loud noises, bright lights

03:05.600 --> 03:08.910
can be especially difficult
for someone like your son.

03:09.120 --> 03:12.317
The shirt, most likely fabric sensitivity.

03:13.800 --> 03:15.597
Hugging,
closeness, touching...

03:15.880 --> 03:16.880
Justine, no shoes today.

03:17.040 --> 03:18.656
That can be a challenge, yes.

03:18.680 --> 03:20.520
When it's somebody else's child,

03:20.640 --> 03:22.198
it's a challenge.

03:22.720 --> 03:24.358
When it's yours,

03:24.520 --> 03:25.794
it's a problem.

03:26.800 --> 03:29.678
My practice focuses on education.

03:29.840 --> 03:32.308
I'd like to work with your son,
at his speed.

03:32.840 --> 03:36.196
Help him develop the skills
he'll need to lead a full life.

03:36.400 --> 03:38.118
Communicating, eye contact,

03:38.320 --> 03:40.231
understanding non-verbal cues,

03:40.400 --> 03:41.833
making friends.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.798
The only friend
he has is his little brother.

03:45.480 --> 03:48.313
I'm sure moving from base to base
hasn 't helped.

03:49.080 --> 03:52.993
My husband's in the Army,
which means we all are.

03:54.160 --> 03:57.152
Would you be willing to let your son
stay with us for the summer

03:57.320 --> 04:00.915
free of charge, working with me
in a sensory-friendly environment?

04:01.080 --> 04:02.718
That's not gonna happen.

04:03.520 --> 04:05.988
If loud noises and bright lights
bother him,

04:06.160 --> 04:08.549
he needs more of it, not less.

04:09.320 --> 04:12.357
The world is not
a sensory-friendly place,

04:12.560 --> 04:14.676
and that's where
he needs to learn to live.

04:16.519 --> 04:17.748
Not in here.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.033
Doctor, in your opinion,

04:20.560 --> 04:23.393
can our son lead a normal life?

04:24.200 --> 04:26.236
Define normal.

04:26.680 --> 04:28.511
I need to finish! I need to finish!

