Hmm. Mmm.

05:26.840 --> 05:31.072
I, uh... I never thought of myself
as a quitter... Fourth-generation farmer.

05:33.080 --> 05:36.629
But between the property taxes

05:37.320 --> 05:39.754
and the fertilizer costs, and insurance...

05:44.960 --> 05:46.075
Oh, to hell with it.

05:46.280 --> 05:48.635
What if, just temporarily, mind you,

05:48.800 --> 05:51.633
we put this year's taxes
on our credit card?

05:58.040 --> 05:59.359
Do you like it?

05:59.520 --> 06:00.873
I made it myself.

06:01.040 --> 06:02.598
No, not particularly.

06:03.480 --> 06:04.959
But do you ever sell them?

06:05.120 --> 06:06.599
At church fairs now and again.

06:06.800 --> 06:09.712
Mrs. Rice, you may have what the IRS
calls a "home-based business."

06:09.880 --> 06:12.040
What room do you use in your house
when you make those?

06:12.160 --> 06:13.195
I don't, really.

06:13.360 --> 06:14.998
Just wherever I happen to be, I guess.

06:15.160 --> 06:17.628
In front of the TV,
at the kitchen table.

06:17.800 --> 06:20.176
I like to spread my beads out
in the dining room, but Frank gets...

06:20.200 --> 06:22.475
Yes, it would be better
if you could try to remember

06:22.640 --> 06:24.949
the one specific space that you use.

06:25.200 --> 06:27.316
Your home is 2,913 square feet.

06:27.680 --> 06:30.478
IRS code allows us to deduct
from your taxable income

06:30.640 --> 06:33.313
a percentage of your workspace
relative to your overall home.

06:33.480 --> 06:34.640
- What...
- Mr. Rice...

06:34.960 --> 06:36.518
How big is your dining room?

06:37.160 --> 06:38.388
Mrs. Rice's office.

06:38.800 --> 06:40.880
I wouldn't
so much as call it an office...

06:40.960 --> 06:42.440
Oh.

06:42.800 --> 06:46.395
It's, uh, approximately 200, uh...

06:51.880 --> 06:53.996
Well, make it 300 square feet.

06:54.160 --> 06:55.673
Excellent. Mrs. Rice...

06:55.840 --> 06:56.909
Dolores.

06:57.080 --> 07:00.436
Dolores, when you order supplies,
do you order online?

07:00.600 --> 07:02.989
I don't. I just zip on over
to the bead store.

07:03.160 --> 07:04.388
Zip?

07:04.680 --> 07:07.148
I drive the truck.

07:07.920 --> 07:09.558
The company truck.

07:28.200 --> 07:29.349
Come in.

07:32.040 --> 07:33.656
Mr. King, you have wandered

07:33.680 --> 07:35.272
so far outside your legal purview.

07:35.440 --> 07:36.998
As president of Southern Gulf Bank,

07:37.160 --> 07:39.720
I intend to protect
my customers' privacy...

07:39.880 --> 07:40.915
Stop talking.

07:41.080 --> 07:43.520
You have a very cavalier attitude
for the president of a bank,

07:43.560 --> 07:45.080
with such a piss-poor capital cushion.

07:45.280 --> 07:48.716
Now, I want a record of every transaction
Abayed has had for the past two years.

07:48.880 --> 07:51.553
Deposits, withdrawals,
cashier's checks, credit cards.

07:51.720 --> 07:54.871
Birmingham or Bahrain,
it is now Treasury business.

07:55.040 --> 07:56.393
Goodbye.

07:56.560 --> 07:58.073
Medina.

07:58.240 --> 07:59.593
Am I saying that correctly?

07:59.760 --> 08:00.875
Medina, yes, sir.

08:01.280 --> 08:04.238
I've read all your case files,
Director King.

08:04.400 --> 08:07.073
It's impressive work. Very.

08:07.240 --> 08:10.391
Marybeth Ascension Medina.

08:10.560 --> 08:12.915
Graduated University of Baltimore
cum laude

08:13.080 --> 08:15.116
with a degree in criminal justice.

08:15.280 --> 08:19.831
Two years Baltimore PD as an analyst,
two more at Homeland, analyst again,

08:20.240 --> 08:23.789
and the last five years here at Treasury.

08:23.960 --> 08:25.154
Analyst.

08:26.240 --> 08:29.676
You did the heavy lifting
on Agent Lorenz's case last month.

08:30.440 --> 08:32.431
I worked on it, yeah, but Agent Lorenz...

08:32.600 --> 08:35.273
Why haven't you applied
for promotion to agent?

08:35.760 --> 08:37.273
You're already doing the work.

08:38.280 --> 08:39.918
Analyst is a good fit.

08:40.120 --> 08:43.111
And I enjoy the work, so...

08:44.680 --> 08:47.672
Well, you're a liar, Medina.

08:50.960 --> 08:52.393
Ward of the state of Maryland's

08:52.560 --> 08:54.835
foster care
and juvenile detention systems

08:55.000 --> 08:57.116
from age 11 to 18.

08:57.280 --> 09:00.272
Weapons charges, assault and battery.

09:01.040 --> 09:02.189
Ouch.

09:02.360 --> 09:04.191
Attempted murder.

09:07.840 --> 09:09.558
Those records were sealed.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.552
Is that a nine millimeter?

09:15.560 --> 09:16.629
.45.

09:16.800 --> 09:20.156
You better sit your ass
back down in that chair, young lady.

09:21.000 --> 09:23.150
This is a big moment for you.

09:24.360 --> 09:26.237
Make a good choice.

09:36.320 --> 09:41.314
Lying on a federal employment application
is a felony.

09:43.240 --> 09:48.997
So right now, I'm the only thing standing
between you and significant prison time.

09:52.360 --> 09:54.157
What do you want?

09:54.920 --> 09:57.992
Do you like puzzles, Marybeth Medina?

10:01.280 --> 10:04.511
I meant what I said, son.
You're welcome out to the place anytime.

10:04.680 --> 10:06.318
Do you fish? I got a two-acre pond

10:06.480 --> 10:08.016
that is just thick with catfish and bass...

10:08.040 --> 10:10.349
I don't fish. I shoot.

10:10.520 --> 10:14.195
Well, the farm's a perfect place
to do a little plinkin', so...

10:15.040 --> 10:16.040
Well...

10:16.920 --> 10:18.069
Thank you.

10:19.120 --> 10:20.712
You take care, son.

10:20.880 --> 10:21.949
Thank you.

10:26.400 --> 10:29.472
My daughter's meeting me for lunch.
I think you two just might hit it off.

10:29.640 --> 10:31.039
Nice to see you.

10:33.720 --> 10:34.789
Already enhanced.

10:34.960 --> 10:38.236
Was taken three years ago in Antwerp
by an undercover Interpol agent.

10:38.400 --> 10:40.277
Their target's on the far right.

10:40.600 --> 10:41.874
Yeah, Zalmay Atta.

10:42.600 --> 10:43.635
Go on.

10:44.280 --> 10:46.714
Ran the world's largest opium pipeline.

10:46.880 --> 10:49.394
Ties to Karzai and Ghani, Taliban.

10:49.560 --> 10:51.994
I mean, he was considered untouchable.

10:52.320 --> 10:54.390
Look at the rest. Tell me what you see.

11:02.920 --> 11:05.912
Yeah, I remember most of these arrests.
They were huge.

11:06.080 --> 11:08.230
Focus. They're not all arrests.

11:22.280 --> 11:23.759
It's the same man.

11:23.920 --> 11:25.353
"Lou Carroll."

11:27.080 --> 11:28.911
For what it's worth, it's an alias.

11:29.120 --> 11:31.190
The Hong Kong photo
goes back about five years.

11:31.360 --> 11:33.954
In that one, he's "Carl Gauss."

11:35.080 --> 11:39.437
Tokyo, Tel Aviv, Naples.
There was a sighting in Tehran.

11:39.600 --> 11:41.511
All describing the same man.
"An accountant."

11:41.720 --> 11:44.109
"Our accountant." "The accountant."

11:44.280 --> 11:47.397
The accountant, like CPA accountant?

11:49.360 --> 11:50.475
Okay.

11:51.200 --> 11:53.634
Say you're the head of the Sinaloa Cartel.

11:54.160 --> 11:56.355
Now, the cartels count their money

11:56.520 --> 11:58.670
by weighing it in 18-wheelers.

11:59.320 --> 12:01.117
But one sunny Mexican day,

12:01.320 --> 12:04.949
your in-house money scrubber comes to you
and says you're 30 million light.

12:05.160 --> 12:07.390
Who can you trust to do
the forensic accounting,

12:07.560 --> 12:09.312
track your stolen cash?

12:09.480 --> 12:11.675
Deloitte and Touche? H&R Block?

12:12.800 --> 12:14.631
You somehow

12:14.800 --> 12:17.678
contact an individual
capable of coming in cold,

12:17.880 --> 12:20.155
un-cooking years of books,

12:20.840 --> 12:22.831
and getting out alive.

12:23.160 --> 12:24.798
I retire in seven months.

12:24.960 --> 12:29.670
Before I do, I need to know
who he is, how he does it.

12:29.840 --> 12:32.400
I mean, who survives
this kind of clientele?

12:32.600 --> 12:34.591
The secrets this guy has.

12:36.840 --> 12:39.400
What exactly do you want me to do?

12:40.280 --> 12:42.157
Report directly to me.

12:42.360 --> 12:43.839
No other case work.

12:44.000 --> 12:46.355
No other Treasury personnel involved.

12:46.920 --> 12:50.117
At the end of the month,
one of two things will have occurred.

12:51.040 --> 12:53.031
Resolution of this case,

12:56.120 --> 12:58.395
or we update your photo.

14:37.560 --> 14:39.790
You want it your way?
You got it!

14:46.320 --> 14:47.958
Mom! Mom! Mom!

14:48.120 --> 14:50.315
Mom! Why is Mom leaving? Mom!

14:50.560 --> 14:52.278
Mom! Mom!

14:53.720 --> 14:55.631
- I just got home.
- You're always...

15:05.720 --> 15:06.720
Mom! Why are you leaving?

15:06.960 --> 15:08.136
I'm just asking you to stay.

15:08.160 --> 15:09.456
- Just, please stay.
- We had help!

15:09.480 --> 15:11.520
- Stay here! Don't go anywhere!
- You threw it away!

15:16.440 --> 15:17.555
No. Hey.

15:23.280 --> 15:24.349
That's it.

15:24.520 --> 15:25.880
Please don't leave...

15:26.080 --> 15:27.736
Mom!

15:27.760 --> 15:29.280
Here we go, here we go.

15:29.680 --> 15:30.680
Here we go.

