16:37.600 --> 16:40.239
Looks like somebody's seen
too many westerns.

16:41.440 --> 16:42.953
Yeah, must be what...

16:44.760 --> 16:46.113
A mile out?

16:48.440 --> 16:50.351
Not on my best day...

17:04.400 --> 17:05.752
Holy shit.

18:38.720 --> 18:40.756
Okay, listen to me.

18:40.920 --> 18:44.799
In-flec-tion. Right?
Listen, just listen to my tone.

18:44.960 --> 18:47.793
I say, "Oh, I'm another year older,

18:47.960 --> 18:51.555
"and I don't know if I'm ever gonna
get out of this fucking place."

18:51.720 --> 18:53.199
And you say...

18:53.400 --> 18:55.176
You're probably right, Francis.
You're extremely old.

18:55.200 --> 18:56.696
- It's unlikely you'll survive to...
- No. No...

18:56.720 --> 18:58.870
No. Hold on. That's not what you say.

18:59.440 --> 19:02.034
Two years together
every night, you know.

19:02.240 --> 19:05.277
I gave you a PhD in black money,
but you gotta learn this.

19:05.440 --> 19:07.158
- This is crucial.
- You're frustrated.

19:07.320 --> 19:08.600
- What am I?
- You're frustrated.

19:09.560 --> 19:10.709
That's what I am.

19:10.920 --> 19:12.478
I'm frustrated. Good, good. Excellent.

19:12.920 --> 19:14.956
Finally. All right. Let's do another one.

19:16.560 --> 19:19.757
Lights out, ladies.
Lights out.

19:20.920 --> 19:22.720
Names and addresses. Go.

19:23.560 --> 19:26.996
Semion Ivankov.
79 Primorsky Boulevard, Odessa.

19:27.160 --> 19:31.756
The Meier brothers, Moshe and Itzhak.
221 She'arim Boulevard in Jerusalem.

19:31.920 --> 19:34.673
Dominic Rabito of
960 Court Street, Brooklyn.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.068
Ask for Bobby.

19:36.320 --> 19:37.469
Ask for Bobby.

19:37.800 --> 19:38.880
You know, I'm old.

19:39.000 --> 19:42.276
I may be remembering things
a little rosier than they were.

19:42.640 --> 19:46.519
I mean, you want to fill out 1040s
and itemize deductions,

19:46.680 --> 19:48.760
and pull in 50 grand a year?
I mean, that's a living.

19:48.920 --> 19:51.673
Because if you go down
this road, this road...

19:51.840 --> 19:55.355
You can't go back, you understand?
It's dangerous. Do you understand?

19:55.520 --> 19:56.589
I understand.

19:56.760 --> 19:59.433
You find one person
you can trust, just one.

19:59.600 --> 20:03.479
And do not make my mistake.
You keep moving your ass around.

20:12.200 --> 20:14.191
They gave me a new handler today.

20:15.480 --> 20:17.789
I don't like this guy. He's dull.

20:19.560 --> 20:20.788
Worried.

20:24.880 --> 20:26.313
Ah, fuck it.

20:28.680 --> 20:30.352
Good night, son.

20:31.720 --> 20:33.392
Good night, Francis.

20:41.320 --> 20:43.550
What about Zurich? Saudi Arabia?

20:43.760 --> 20:45.096
The Swiss are cheap.

20:45.120 --> 20:47.520
Dubai is one thing, but we're
too conspicuous in the Kingdom.

20:47.680 --> 20:48.715
I vote Chicago.

20:48.880 --> 20:51.872
- Why?
- There's an uptick in online chatter.

20:52.040 --> 20:53.189
People looking for you.

20:53.360 --> 20:55.510
- What people?
- The unfriendly kind.

20:55.960 --> 20:57.996
Let's try a legitimate client for once.

20:58.160 --> 21:01.914
No cartels, arms brokers,
money launderers, assassins.

21:02.360 --> 21:04.920
I like safe. I like you safe.

21:05.080 --> 21:06.600
Everyone's hiding something.

21:06.680 --> 21:08.432
At least there's honor among thieves.

21:08.600 --> 21:11.751
There's honor among Illinois
electronics manufacturers.

21:12.560 --> 21:16.678
They're in your current backyard.
No risk of movement. You'll meet?

21:17.640 --> 21:18.709
Yeah, I'll meet.

21:19.280 --> 21:20.918
One last piece of business.

21:21.080 --> 21:22.229
Just the Renoir.

21:22.400 --> 21:24.120
I don't have
a buyer for the Renoir.

21:24.280 --> 21:27.352
The Pollock can move.
Will you ever let it go?

21:29.760 --> 21:30.760
Hello?

21:30.920 --> 21:33.354
Just the Renoir. Drop the price.

21:34.880 --> 21:36.233
Heavy sigh.

21:38.120 --> 21:40.270
Go to work, dreamboat.

21:47.920 --> 21:50.753
Now, Mr. Wolff, I half-suspect
we're wasting your time.

21:50.920 --> 21:52.433
I'm quite sure you're not.

21:52.600 --> 21:54.113
And you know this how?

21:54.280 --> 21:55.872
I'm on the clock.

21:56.840 --> 21:58.068
Shit.

21:58.240 --> 22:00.071
I hope we're not wasting ours then.

22:01.400 --> 22:05.393
Look, kidding aside, I think if you
saw our books, you'd run for the hills.

22:06.760 --> 22:09.274
We have an incredibly complicated
accounting system.

22:09.440 --> 22:11.908
Depreciation schedules
on hundreds of different items.

22:12.080 --> 22:13.957
Full-time and contract employees.

22:14.120 --> 22:16.111
Department of Defense classified accounts.

22:16.280 --> 22:17.429
It's a numerical shitstorm.

22:17.600 --> 22:20.433
I'll need to see all those books
for the past 10 years.

22:20.600 --> 22:23.239
Bank statements, complete list
of clients and vendors.

22:23.440 --> 22:26.352
Hard copies printed out, my eyes only.
All the information's right here.

22:26.600 --> 22:27.828
Okay, well, well, look.

22:28.000 --> 22:30.833
This all came to my attention
only last week.

22:31.000 --> 22:33.958
Now, a junior cost accountant
stuck her nose where it didn't belong,

22:34.160 --> 22:36.151
and obviously had no idea
what she was looking at.

22:36.440 --> 22:38.590
Lamar's overreacting.
There's no missing money.

22:38.760 --> 22:41.115
How long have you been CFO
of this company, sir?

22:41.280 --> 22:42.349
15 years.

22:42.520 --> 22:44.556
I need the books for the past 15, please.

22:45.120 --> 22:47.111
Well, you're awful goddamn blunt!

22:47.280 --> 22:49.794
I'm Lamar Blackburn's oldest friend.

22:49.960 --> 22:50.960
I've been by his side

22:51.120 --> 22:54.430
since he was turning out RC robots
that RadioShack called crap.

22:54.800 --> 22:57.109
I wouldn't take a dime without his say-so.

22:57.960 --> 22:59.029
You're angry.

22:59.200 --> 23:00.519
Oh, this is bullshit.

23:01.320 --> 23:04.312
Unusual way of making contact with you,
Mr. Wolff.

23:05.960 --> 23:07.951
You were recommended by Mansoor Haqqani.

23:08.120 --> 23:10.509
We custom-made prosthetics
for his youngest daughter.

23:11.160 --> 23:12.912
You may know that she lost both legs

23:13.120 --> 23:15.634
to a car bomb
outside his investment firm in Lahore.

